hpnicfFlash.name: hpnicfFlash
hpnicfFlash.description: This MIB contains objects to manage flash cards and flash card operations. There are no constraints on this MIB.

HpnicfFlashOperationStatus.name: HpnicfFlashOperationStatus
HpnicfFlashOperationStatus.description: The status of the specified operation can be one of the following. opInProgress : The operation is in process. opSuccess : The operation has been completed successfully. opInvalid : The command is invalid or command-protocol-device combination is unsupported by the system. opInvalidProtocol : Invalid protocol is specified. opInvalidSourceName : Invalid source file name is specified. opInvalidDestName : Invalid target name is specified. opInvalidServerAddress : Invalid server address is specified. opDeviceBusy : The device is in use and locked by another process. opDeviceOpenError : Invalid device name is specified. opDeviceError : Device read, write or erase error. opDeviceNotProgrammable : Device is read-only but a write or erase operation was specified. opDeviceFull : Device is filled to capacity. opFileOpenError : Invalid file name; file not found in partition. opFileTransferError : File transfer was unsuccessful. opFileChecksumError : File checksum in Flash is invalid. opNoMemory : System is running in low on memory. opUnknownFailure : Failure which is unknown. opDeleteFileOpenError : File is in used by another process. opDeleteInvalidDevice : Invalid device name is specified. opDeleteInvalidFunction : Deleted operation is unsupported by the device. opDeleteOperationError : Operation is in a low error. opDeleteInvalidFileName : Invalid file name is specified. pDeleteDeviceBusy : The device is in use and locked by another process. opDeleteParaError : The parameters are invalid. opDeleteInvalidPath : The file path is invalid. opDeleteFileNotExistInSlave : Failed to delete file, because the file is not exist in the slave. opDeleteFileFailedInSlave : Operation is fail when delete file in the slave. opSlaveFull : Operation is fail for the slave don't have enough space. opCopyToSlaveFailure : Operation is fail when copy file to the slave.

HpnicfFlashPartitionUpgradeMode.name: HpnicfFlashPartitionUpgradeMode
HpnicfFlashPartitionUpgradeMode.description: Flash partition upgrade method, i.e., method by which new files can be downloaded into the partition. FLH stands for Flash Load Helper, a feature provided on run-from-Flash systems for upgrading Flash. This feature uses the bootstrap code in ROMs to help in automatic download. This object should be retrieved if the partition status is runFromFlash(2). If the partition status is readOnly(1), the upgrade method would depend on the reason for the readOnly status. For example, it may simply be a matter of installing the programming jumper, or it may require execution of a later version of software that supports the Flash chips. unknown - the current system image does not know how Flash can be programmed. A possible method would be to reload the ROM image and perform the upgrade manually. rxbootFLH - the Flash Load Helper is available to download files to Flash. A copy-to-flash command can be used and this system image will automatically reload the Rxboot image in ROM and direct it to carry out the download request. direct - will be done directly by this image.

HpnicfFlashPartitionStatus.name: HpnicfFlashPartitionStatus
HpnicfFlashPartitionStatus.description: If device is not programmable the value of it will be 'readOnly'; If the current image is running from this partition the value of it will be 'runFromFlash' If device is programmable the value of it will be 'readWrite'.

hpnicfFlhSupportNum.name: hpnicfFlhSupportNum
hpnicfFlhSupportNum.description: Specifies the total number of flash which the system supported. The MIB should not be loaded if there is no flash in the system and so the value here will be a minimum of 1.

hpnicfFlashTable.name: hpnicfFlashTable
hpnicfFlashTable.description: This table gives the properties of all the flashes on the system.

hpnicfFlhIndex.name: hpnicfFlhIndex
hpnicfFlhIndex.description: The index of hpnicfFlashTable. There are two parts for this index depicted as follows: 31 15 0 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ + entity index + random index + + ( bit 16..31 ) ( bit 0..15 ) + +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ From bit0 to bit15 (two bytes), it has a minimum value of 1, and maximum value of the same as the value of hpnicfFlhSupportNum. From bit16 to bit31 (two bytes), it is the physical index the same as the entPhysicalIndex specified in ENTITY-MIB.

hpnicfFlhSize.name: hpnicfFlhSize
hpnicfFlhSize.description: Specifies the total size of the flash indexed by hpnicfFlhIndex. The value should be zero if the flash is removed for a removable device. If the total size of the flash exceeds 2,147,483,647 bytes, hpnicfFlhHCSize specifies the actual size.

hpnicfFlhPos.name: hpnicfFlhPos
hpnicfFlhPos.description: The position of the flash device in system. This object is an index of entPhysicalTable in ENTITY-MIB. If the value of this object is 0, the main processor is indicated.

hpnicfFlhName.name: hpnicfFlhName
hpnicfFlhName.description: The flash name within the system.

hpnicfFlhChipNum.name: hpnicfFlhChipNum
hpnicfFlhChipNum.description: The chip numbers in the flash.

hpnicfFlhDescr.name: hpnicfFlhDescr
hpnicfFlhDescr.description: Description of the purpose of the flash in the system.

hpnicfFlhInitTime.name: hpnicfFlhInitTime
hpnicfFlhInitTime.description: The initialization time for the flash component or partition, recorded using the system time. This will be the boot time for a fixed device. For a removable component or a partition, it will be the initialization time.

hpnicfFlhRemovable.name: hpnicfFlhRemovable
hpnicfFlhRemovable.description: The value indicates whether the flash indexed can be removed or not. The true(1) value indicates the flash device CAN be removed.

hpnicfFlhPartitionBool.name: hpnicfFlhPartitionBool
hpnicfFlhPartitionBool.description: The value indicates whether the flash indexed can be partitioned or not. The true(1) value indicates the flash CAN be partitioned.

hpnicfFlhMinPartitionSize.name: hpnicfFlhMinPartitionSize
hpnicfFlhMinPartitionSize.description: Minimum partition size supported. If hpnicfFlhDevicePartitionBool is false, the value of this object is the same as hpnicfFlhSize.

hpnicfFlhMaxPartitions.name: hpnicfFlhMaxPartitions
hpnicfFlhMaxPartitions.description: The maximum count of partitions which the system supports for this flash. If hpnicfFlhPartitionBool is false, the object value is 1.

hpnicfFlhPartitionNum.name: hpnicfFlhPartitionNum
hpnicfFlhPartitionNum.description: The actual number of partitions supported by the system for this flash. If hpnicfFlhPartitionBool is false, this value is 1.

hpnicfFlhKbyteSize.name: hpnicfFlhKbyteSize
hpnicfFlhKbyteSize.description: Specifies the total size of the flash device indexed by hpnicfFlhIndex. The value should be zero if the flash is removed for a removable device.

hpnicfFlhHCSize.name: hpnicfFlhHCSize
hpnicfFlhHCSize.description: Specifies the total size of the flash indexed by hpnicfFlhIndex. This node is a 64-bit substitute for hpnicfFlhSize.

hpnicfFlhChipTable.name: hpnicfFlhChipTable
hpnicfFlhChipTable.description: Table of properties for all flash chips. Used mainly for diagnostics.

hpnicfFlhChipID.name: hpnicfFlhChipID
hpnicfFlhChipID.description: The manufacturer code (the upper byte) and device code (the lower byte) for a chip. Unknown chip code is presented as 00:00.

hpnicfFlhChipDescr.name: hpnicfFlhChipDescr
hpnicfFlhChipDescr.description: The description of the flash chip.

hpnicfFlhChipWriteTimesLimit.name: hpnicfFlhChipWriteTimesLimit
hpnicfFlhChipWriteTimesLimit.description: The limit for the number of write times (retries) for a flash chip. If the limit is exceeded an error should be reported by the management station.

hpnicfFlhChipWriteTimes.name: hpnicfFlhChipWriteTimes
hpnicfFlhChipWriteTimes.description: A count of write times (retries) for the flash chip since initialization. A count of 25 or more for a single chip indicates a write error. Management stations should note the value of this MIB before and after a write operation, and report any errors accordingly.

hpnicfFlhChipEraseTimesLimit.name: hpnicfFlhChipEraseTimesLimit
hpnicfFlhChipEraseTimesLimit.description: The limit for the number of erase times (retries) for a flash chip. If the limit is exceeded an error should be reported by the management station.

hpnicfFlhChipEraseTimes.name: hpnicfFlhChipEraseTimes
hpnicfFlhChipEraseTimes.description: A count of erase times (retries) for the flash chip since initialization. A count of 2000 or more for a single chip indicates a write error. Management stations should note the value of this MIB before and after an erase operation, and report any errors accordingly.

hpnicfFlhPartitionTable.name: hpnicfFlhPartitionTable
hpnicfFlhPartitionTable.description: Properties for the flash partitions. Minimum of one entry in this table.

hpnicfFlhPartitionEntry.name: hpnicfFlhPartitionEntry
hpnicfFlhPartitionEntry.description: An entry of the hpnicfFlhPartitionTable.Indexed by flash number and partition number.

hpnicfFlhPartIndex.name: hpnicfFlhPartIndex
hpnicfFlhPartIndex.description: An index which specifies a sequenced partition in the system.

hpnicfFlhPartFirstChip.name: hpnicfFlhPartFirstChip
hpnicfFlhPartFirstChip.description: The first chip's sequence number in the partition, by which a chip can be indexed in chip table.

hpnicfFlhPartLastChip.name: hpnicfFlhPartLastChip
hpnicfFlhPartLastChip.description: The last chip's sequence number in the partition, by which a chip can be indexed in chip table.

hpnicfFlhPartSpace.name: hpnicfFlhPartSpace
hpnicfFlhPartSpace.description: The total space of the flash partition. The following should be satisfied: hpnicfFlhPartSpace = n*hpnicfFlhMinPartitionSize If the total size of the flash partition exceeds 2,147,483,647 bytes, hpnicfFlhPartHCSpace specifies the actual size.

hpnicfFlhPartSpaceFree.name: hpnicfFlhPartSpaceFree
hpnicfFlhPartSpaceFree.description: The flash partition's free space. If the free space of the flash partition exceeds 2,147,483,647 bytes, hpnicfFlhPartHCSpaceFree specifies the actual free space.

hpnicfFlhPartFileNum.name: hpnicfFlhPartFileNum
hpnicfFlhPartFileNum.description: The number of all the files in the flash partition.

hpnicfFlhPartChecksumMethod.name: hpnicfFlhPartChecksumMethod
hpnicfFlhPartChecksumMethod.description: The Checksum method which the file system uses.

hpnicfFlhPartUpgradeMode.name: hpnicfFlhPartUpgradeMode
hpnicfFlhPartUpgradeMode.description: The upgrade mode of the Flash partition

hpnicfFlhPartName.name: hpnicfFlhPartName
hpnicfFlhPartName.description: The name of the flash partition given by the system.

hpnicfFlhPartRequireErase.name: hpnicfFlhPartRequireErase
hpnicfFlhPartRequireErase.description: Shows whether a write operation is conditional on partition erase.

hpnicfFlhPartFileNameLen.name: hpnicfFlhPartFileNameLen
hpnicfFlhPartFileNameLen.description: The maximum length of file name supported in the system.

hpnicfFlhPartBootable.name: hpnicfFlhPartBootable
hpnicfFlhPartBootable.description: The value indicates whether the partition is a bootable partition. The true(1) value indicates a bootable partition.

hpnicfFlhPartPathForGlobalOpt.name: hpnicfFlhPartPathForGlobalOpt
hpnicfFlhPartPathForGlobalOpt.description: The value indicates whether the partition is used in a global file operation. The true(1) value indicates that in one global file operation files will be copied to or deleted from this partition. When hpnicfFlhPartPathForGlobalOpt in one entry is set to true(1), hpnicfFlhPartPathForGlobalOpt in other entries with the same entity index will be set to false(0).

hpnicfFlhPartHCSpace.name: hpnicfFlhPartHCSpace
hpnicfFlhPartHCSpace.description: The total space of the flash partition. This node is a 64-bit substitue for hpnicfFlhPartSpace.

hpnicfFlhPartHCSpaceFree.name: hpnicfFlhPartHCSpaceFree
hpnicfFlhPartHCSpaceFree.description: The flash partition's free space. This node is a 64-bit substitue for hpnicfFlhPartSpace.

hpnicfFlhFileEntry.name: hpnicfFlhFileEntry
hpnicfFlhFileEntry.description: An entry representing a file. Indexed using flash number, partition number, and file number.

hpnicfFlhFileIndex.name: hpnicfFlhFileIndex
hpnicfFlhFileIndex.description: Index of the table, whose range is from 1 to 2147483647

hpnicfFlhFileName.name: hpnicfFlhFileName
hpnicfFlhFileName.description: A valid file name supported by the file system.

hpnicfFlhFileSize.name: hpnicfFlhFileSize
hpnicfFlhFileSize.description: The file size in bytes excluding the file header of file system. The value should be greater than zero. If the file size exceeds 2,147,483,647 bytes, hpnicfFlhFileHCSize specifies the actual size.

hpnicfFlhFileStatus.name: hpnicfFlhFileStatus
hpnicfFlhFileStatus.description: The status should be as follows: deleted(1): The file is in recycle bin. invalidChecksum(2): The checksum of file is invalid; valid(3): A valid file.

hpnicfFlhFileChecksum.name: hpnicfFlhFileChecksum
hpnicfFlhFileChecksum.description: The file checksum in the header of file.

hpnicfFlhFileHCSize.name: hpnicfFlhFileHCSize
hpnicfFlhFileHCSize.description: The file size in bytes. This node is a 64-bit substitue for hpnicfFlhFileSize.

hpnicfFlhOpEntry.name: hpnicfFlhOpEntry
hpnicfFlhOpEntry.description: Note an operation can not be stopped until it is finished. If notification is configured, NMS will receive a notification at the end of the operation. Entries in the table will be removed automatically in 5 minutes. It can also be deleted by NMS directly.

hpnicfFlhOperIndex.name: hpnicfFlhOperIndex
hpnicfFlhOperIndex.description: Specifies the index of an entry. It is a random value when creating an entry.

hpnicfFlhOperType.name: hpnicfFlhOperType
hpnicfFlhOperType.description: Specifies the operation to be executed. net2FlashWithErase Copy a file to flash; erase flash beforehand. net2FlashWithoutErase Copy a file to flash; do not erase flash beforehand. flash2Net Copy a file from flash. delete Delete a file from flash, the file name is specified by hpnicfFlhOperSourceFile; rename Change a file's name.

hpnicfFlhOperProtocol.name: hpnicfFlhOperProtocol
hpnicfFlhOperProtocol.description: Specifies the protocol used to transfer file. The default protocol is ftp. when 'clusterftp' or 'clustertftp' is selected, the hpnicfFlhOperServerAddress needn't be set, the server address can be acquired automatically, the value of hpnicfFlhOperServerAddress is uncertain during operation. Both member switch and commander switch can use them if they support HGMP v2.

hpnicfFlhOperServerAddress.name: hpnicfFlhOperServerAddress
hpnicfFlhOperServerAddress.description: The address of remote host acting as server for operation. The default value is 255.255.255.255 This object is replaced by hpnicfFlhOperSrvAddrRev for it only support IPv4.

hpnicfFlhOperServerUser.name: hpnicfFlhOperServerUser
hpnicfFlhOperServerUser.description: When using ftp to transfer files, the user name must be specified through this node.

hpnicfFlhOperPassword.name: hpnicfFlhOperPassword
hpnicfFlhOperPassword.description: Remote user password for copying via ftp protocol. Optionally, This object may be ignored for protocols other than ftp.

hpnicfFlhOperSourceFile.name: hpnicfFlhOperSourceFile
hpnicfFlhOperSourceFile.description: Specifies the source file name to be transferred. It may be located on flash or remote server. It may include the file path if it is applicable. It must be specified.

hpnicfFlhOperDestinationFile.name: hpnicfFlhOperDestinationFile
hpnicfFlhOperDestinationFile.description: Specifies the destination file name. It may be located on flash or remote server. It may include the file path if it is applicable. If it is not specified, the destination file name is the same as source file name for application.

hpnicfFlhOperEndNotification.name: hpnicfFlhOperEndNotification
hpnicfFlhOperEndNotification.description: If the value of it is specified 'true', a notification will be generated at the end of the operation. Else no notification will be generated.

hpnicfFlhOperProgress.name: hpnicfFlhOperProgress
hpnicfFlhOperProgress.description: The progress described as the time taken for the operation.

hpnicfFlhOperRowStatus.name: hpnicfFlhOperRowStatus
hpnicfFlhOperRowStatus.description: The row status of this table entry.

hpnicfFlhOperServerPort.name: hpnicfFlhOperServerPort
hpnicfFlhOperServerPort.description: The port of remote host acting as server for operation. If the value of this object is not specified, the server port is the known protocol port.

hpnicfFlhOperSrvAddrType.name: hpnicfFlhOperSrvAddrType
hpnicfFlhOperSrvAddrType.description: The type of IP address for hpnicfFlhOperSrvAddrRev.

hpnicfFlhOperSrvAddrRev.name: hpnicfFlhOperSrvAddrRev
hpnicfFlhOperSrvAddrRev.description: The address of remote host acting as server for operation.

hpnicfFlhOperSrvVPNName.name: hpnicfFlhOperSrvVPNName
hpnicfFlhOperSrvVPNName.description: The VPN instance of this operation uses.

hpnicfFlhOperNotification.name: hpnicfFlhOperNotification
hpnicfFlhOperNotification.description: A hpnicfFlhOperNotification is sent at the completion of a flash copy operation if hpnicfFlhOperEndNotification is true.

hpnicfFlhMIBCompliance.name: hpnicfFlhMIBCompliance
hpnicfFlhMIBCompliance.description: The statement of compliance for those implementing this MIB.

hpnicfFlhGroup.name: hpnicfFlhGroup
hpnicfFlhGroup.description: A collection of objects on Flash level information.

hpnicfFlhChipGroup.name: hpnicfFlhChipGroup
hpnicfFlhChipGroup.description: A collection of objects on chip level information.

hpnicfFlhPartitionGroup.name: hpnicfFlhPartitionGroup
hpnicfFlhPartitionGroup.description: A collection of objects providing on partition level information.

hpnicfFlhFileGroup.name: hpnicfFlhFileGroup
hpnicfFlhFileGroup.description: A collection of objects on file level information.

hpnicfFlhOperationGroup.name: hpnicfFlhOperationGroup
hpnicfFlhOperationGroup.description: A collection of objects of flash operations.

hpnicfFlhNotificationGroup.name: hpnicfFlhNotificationGroup
hpnicfFlhNotificationGroup.description: The collection of notifications in the module
